vels of the program build on each other. Level I provides foundational knowledge and teaches the use of investment tools; Level II focuses on application of concepts and analysis, particularly in the valuation of assets; and Level III builds toward synthesis across topics with an emphasis on portfolio management.', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=habIDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'John Wiley & Sons', DEFAULT, 'CFA Program Curriculum 2017 Level I', '2016-08-01');
